# Utility functions

def price_data(pipeline_output, start=TRAIN_START, end=TEST_START):
    tickerlist = pipeline_output.index.levels[1].unique()
    # Subtract/add one month from bounds
    start_minus_one = datetime.strftime(datetime.strptime(start, "%Y-%m-%d") - timedelta(30), "%Y-%m-%d")
    end_plus_one = datetime.strftime(datetime.strptime(end, "%Y-%m-%d") + timedelta(30), "%Y-%m-%d")
    
    return get_pricing(symbols=tickerlist, start_date=start_minus_one, end_date=end_plus_one, fields="open_price"
    )
In [3]:
def make_pipeline():
    min_mcap = 100e6
    
    sector = RBICSFocus.l1_name.latest
    sector_mask = (sector != "Finance") & (sector != "Utilities")
    mask = QTradableStocksUS() & (Fundamentals.mkt_val_public.latest > min_mcap) & sector_mask
    
    ebit = Fundamentals.ebit_oper_ltm.latest
    ev = Fundamentals.entrpr_val_qf.latest
    earnings_yield = ebit / ev
    
    net_fixed_assets = Fundamentals.ppe_net.latest
    working_capital = Fundamentals.wkcap_qf.latest
    roc = ebit / (net_fixed_assets + working_capital)
    
    ey_rank = earnings_yield.rank(mask=mask)
    roc_rank = roc.rank(mask=mask)
    
    combined_score = ey_rank / ey_rank.max() + roc_rank/roc_rank.max()

    longs = combined_score.top(30, mask=mask)
    
    return Pipeline(
      columns={"longs": longs,
               "signal": combined_score,
                "earnings_yield": earnings_yield,
                "roc": roc,
               "sector": sector
                },
      screen=(mask & combined_score.notnull())
    )

pipeline_out = run_pipeline(pipeline=make_pipeline(), start_date=TRAIN_START, end_date=TEST_START)
factor_data = pipeline_out["signal"]
sector = pipeline_out["sector"]
